                            /     FreePOPs     /
                           /__________________/
			   

* What is this? *

  FreePOPs is an extendible pop3 server. Its main purpose is to provide a pop3
  interface to a webmail. 

* Source organization

  modules/ contains libs needed by freepops. The most are simple, some are
    vanilla distribution of other softwares, in tar.gz format, with a patch,
    other are bindings for lua of other modules, some a simply .lua files
    collections.
  src/ contains the C main code that hasn't sense to put in a library
  src/lua/ contains .lua files needed at runtime by freepops.
  config generated by ./configure.sh
  config.h edit to change global #defines
  config.lua edit to configure plugin settings

